race.comment: TOFINO (5) exceeded market expectation last start, and the form around that race has since held up strongly. She strips fitter third-up and draws far kinder. Big chance to repeat the dose. WILD WILLY (2) has built nicely this prep and should be at his peak now. The rise in trip suits, Opperman sticks, and he gets a terrific chance to finally snap a long run of outs. SPIRIT OF FLIGHT (6) has also been below her best of late, but this shapes as the right race to rebound. The 3kg claim gets her in light, and she's the type who can burst through late if things fall her way. GRINZINGER ALLEE (13) was too bad to be true last time but was ticking along nicely prior. Gets in light with the claims and is worth another chance.
